    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-29T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-29T21:00:00-05:00" n="334"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.51/957: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-29T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 29, 1939—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. It will be a serious embarrassment if I do not receive reply immediately to
                    my cables in regard to the Bolivian advance and I earnestly hope it will enable
                    me to enter into satisfactory exchange of letters tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
